-- Morocco's major banks, BMCE, BCP, plan Islamic subsidiaries-sources
-- By Aziz El Yaakoubi
-- Sun Mar 23, 2014 10:14AM EDT
-- None



RABAT, March 23 (Reuters) - Two of Morocco's biggest banks, BMCE <BMCE.CS> and BCP <BCP.CS> are preparing to launch Islamic subsidiaries as the Moroccan parliament discusses a bill regulating Islamic banks and sukuk issues, banking sources said.

